# 🚀 Nova CI-Rescue — Self‑Healing CI/CD


**Actions/GitLab/Buildkite run your checks; Nova makes them pass — safely, automatically.**

Not a coding copilot. A shipping copilot.

Nova CI-Rescue is an autonomous CI/CD autopatcher. On every pull request, Nova reproduces failures, maps them to likely fixes, proposes a minimal diff, commits on a safe side branch, and re‑runs your pipeline until the suite is green (or a safety limit is reached).

Result: PRs arrive shippable, with full auditability and guardrails.

> **Note**: This is the first public release of Nova CI-Rescue. Prior internal development history was not published to ensure a clean, secure, and professional open source launch.

## 🎉 What's New in v0.2.0

- **Custom CI Commands**: Use `--ci` flag to specify custom test commands beyond pytest
- **JUnit Report Output**: Generate JUnit XML reports with `--junit-report` for CI/CD integration
- **Enhanced Safety Controls**: Stricter safety limits by default with `--no-safety-limits` override
- **Better Test Discovery**: Improved recursive test discovery for complex project structures

